    <div class="field field-name-body field-type-text-with-summary field-label-hidden view-mode-teaser"><div class="field-items"><div class="field-item even" property="content:encoded"> <p>Around 6 months ago, I introduced <a href="http://fuseinteractive.ca/blog/introducing-seed-drush-based-server-management">Seed</a>, our Drush-based Drupal development server environment. Seed allows you to take care of a lot of tedious tasks of operating a Drupal development server, like setting up virtual hosts and creating MySQL databases, via a simple command-line interface. Today, I'm taking a look at some of the improvements and features that has gone in to Seed since then to help make your development workflow easier.</p> </div></div></div>
